Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update APT and install Python + pip
    apt-get update -y
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        ca-certificates \
        build-essential

    # Install Python packages needed for the course and for the grader
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir --upgrade \
        pytest \
        pulp

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare the filesystem layout expected by the grading tests
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    mkdir -p /home/user/capacity/data

    # workloads.csv
    cat << 'EOF' > /home/user/capacity/data/workloads.csv
workload,cpu,ram,storage
Analytics,4,16,50
Web,2,8,20
Database,6,24,100
Batch,3,12,40
EOF

    # servers.csv
    cat << 'EOF' > /home/user/capacity/data/servers.csv
server,cpu,ram,storage,cost
alpha,8,32,200,50
bravo,16,64,500,90
charlie,4,16,100,30
delta,6,24,120,40
EOF

    # Ensure permissive read permissions (the container will run unprivileged)
    chmod -R a+rX /home/user

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author Capacity-Planning-Container
    Description Base image for the capacity-planning optimisation task

%help
    This Apptainer image contains:
      • Python 3 with pip
      • pytest (for the grader)
      • pulp (MILP modelling library with CBC solver)

    Pre-populated files:
      /home/user/capacity/data/workloads.csv
      /home/user/capacity/data/servers.csv

    The /home/user/capacity/output and /home/user/capacity/logs directories
    are intentionally NOT created; they must be generated by the student's
    solution script at run-time.